<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-8889] CQL spec is missing doc for support of bind variables for LIMIT, TTL, and TIMESTAMP</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-8889</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-4450&quot; title=&quot;CQL3: Allow preparing the consistency level, timestamp and ttl&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-4450&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-4450&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; added the ability to specify a bind variable for the integer value of a LIMIT, TTL, or TIMESTAMP option, but the CQL spec has not been updated to reflect this enhancement.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, the special predefined bind variable names are not documented in the CQL spec: &quot;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;limit&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&quot;, &quot;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;ttl&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&quot;, and &quot;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;timestamp&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
